in the Oval Office.

30:00.973 --> 30:02.757
Mike Pence!

30:02.801 --> 30:04.933
Where is Mikey Pence?!

30:04.977 --> 30:07.936
All the presidential portraits
are staring at me!

30:07.980 --> 30:11.244
And no one will tell me
which one is Hamilton.

30:11.287 --> 30:13.812
- You called for me,
Mr. President?

30:13.855 --> 30:16.379
What's the latest
on the evangelicals?

30:16.423 --> 30:17.728
Are they still with me?

30:17.772 --> 30:19.121
Till the end of the world.

30:19.165 --> 30:20.340
Or November.

30:20.383 --> 30:21.907
Whichever comes first.

30:21.950 --> 30:23.473
Good, good.

30:23.517 --> 30:27.260
Then I can have
some executive time.

30:29.175 --> 30:30.741
Who's at the door?

30:30.785 --> 30:32.221
Is that the pizza guy?

30:33.919 --> 30:35.224
Thank you.

30:35.268 --> 30:37.879
I smelled hamberders.

30:41.927 --> 30:44.973
♪

30:59.422 --> 31:01.207
Scuse me!

31:04.297 --> 31:06.952
It's disgusting,
the way they write about Meghan

31:06.995 --> 31:08.364
compared to the way
they write about Kate.

31:08.388 --> 31:10.129
Well, it is
the British tabloids.

31:10.172 --> 31:11.957
The one-drop rule
is alive and well.

31:12.000 --> 31:13.784
Imagine if Meghan
didn't straighten her hair.

31:15.395 --> 31:16.831
- Okay, where are we?
- It's you.

31:16.875 --> 31:18.354
- I call.
- Pair of sixes.

31:18.398 --> 31:20.530
- I got nothing.
- Read 'em and weep, ladies.

31:20.574 --> 31:23.142
- Full house, twos and nines.
- Damn it.

31:23.185 --> 31:24.317
Three fives.

31:24.360 --> 31:25.535
Lucca?

31:26.972 --> 31:30.410
I swear,
this has never happened to me.

31:30.453 --> 31:32.803
- Oh, just put 'em down.
- What?

31:32.847 --> 31:34.457
Four jacks.

31:35.545 --> 31:37.156
Wow!

31:37.199 --> 31:39.549
Well, go ahead,
take the pot, bitch.

31:39.593 --> 31:42.335
- Okay, sushi break.
- A short one.

31:42.378 --> 31:44.903
Give me time to win it back.

31:46.078 --> 31:48.123
Um, no, Bianca, I...

31:48.167 --> 31:51.344
- I can't take this.
- Sure you can.

31:51.387 --> 31:53.148
They can afford it.
Plus, they're having a blast.

31:53.172 --> 31:55.478
Uh, yeah, but, uh, it wasn't
my money to start with,

31:55.522 --> 31:57.524
- it was yours.-So?
If someone gives you money

31:57.567 --> 31:59.352
to go to a carnival, and you win

31:59.395 --> 32:01.876
a stuffed animal or a goldfish,
do you give it back?

32:01.920 --> 32:04.487
Yeah, but this-this is nota
goldfish or a stuffed animal.

32:04.531 --> 32:06.489
How about I quit,

32:06.533 --> 32:09.405
- and youplay with my winnings.
- No. You're being ridiculous.

32:09.449 --> 32:11.973
You can pay me back the
original50, but the rest is yours.

32:12.017 --> 32:14.976
Look, if you're
that uncomfortable, just lose.

32:16.369 --> 32:18.980
Okay. So, how much is there?

32:19.024 --> 32:20.112
Half a million.

32:20.155 --> 32:21.852
What?

32:21.896 --> 32:23.854
But don't forget: 20%...

32:23.898 --> 32:25.856
goes to charity.

32:47.400 --> 32:49.402
♪

32:54.450 --> 32:56.061
Out.

33:02.589 --> 33:03.938
Call.

33:05.157 --> 33:07.115
- Let's see it.
- I have nothing.

33:07.159 --> 33:09.030
Two threes.

33:10.249 --> 33:12.381
Damn it. It's yours.

33:12.425 --> 33:13.600
What? What-what do you have?

33:13.643 --> 33:15.036
Nothing.

33:15.080 --> 33:16.907
It's yours, Lucca!

33:16.951 --> 33:18.561
Congratulations!

33:18.605 --> 33:21.912
A million and a half dollars!

33:21.956 --> 33:23.436
♪

33:29.007 --> 33:31.226
- We got a problem.
- What?

33:31.270 --> 33:33.011
Trump's Twitter feed?

33:33.054 --> 33:34.360
Damn. "Sergeant Meyer

33:34.403 --> 33:35.926
"is one of our great fighters.

33:35.970 --> 33:38.364
"Effective immediately,
I'm pardoning him

33:38.407 --> 33:41.280
- so he can continue to serve
this great country."
Jesus.

33:41.323 --> 33:43.195
"Stop hounding him,

33:43.238 --> 33:44.500
and get back to business."

33:49.679 --> 33:53.118
Okay, okay,
so we-we still havethe squad members

33:53.161 --> 33:56.077
to testify to what Meyer did;
the pardon doesn't matter.

33:56.121 --> 33:57.687
No. They're not testifying.

33:57.731 --> 33:59.646
- What? How do you know?
- I called them.

33:59.689 --> 34:01.450
First thing I did.
They're worried about Meyer,

34:01.474 --> 34:03.495
now that he's pardoned,
that he's gonna come after them.

34:03.519 --> 34:05.260
Oh, my God.

34:05.304 --> 34:08.959
These guys fight terrorists
and they dismantle IEDs.

34:09.003 --> 34:12.963
- I don't understandwhy they're afraid
to speak up.-It's not cowardice.

34:13.007 --> 34:14.680
Meyer keeps his command, he's
back to being their superior.

34:14.704 --> 34:17.142
They got to work with him again.
They may have to work

34:17.185 --> 34:20.188
- with him for years.-All right, that...
makes sense.

34:20.232 --> 34:22.277
You know, there is...

34:22.321 --> 34:26.020
one witness we can call now.

34:30.416 --> 34:31.721
Thank you.

34:39.729 --> 34:41.731
Wake up, Cinderella.

34:43.777 --> 34:45.344
Ten-hut!

34:47.520 --> 34:49.043
At ease.

34:49.087 --> 34:52.090
Does the defense
have anything else?

34:52.133 --> 34:53.502
We have one more witness,
Your Honor.

34:53.526 --> 34:55.373
The defense recalls
Sergeant Meyer to the stand.

34:55.397 --> 34:57.399
The defense has already wasted
the court's time

34:57.443 --> 35:00.098
-with this cynical tactic,
Your Honor.
-The sergeant made it clear

35:00.141 --> 35:02.032
- he would not answer
your questions, Ms. Reddick.
- Yes.

35:02.056 --> 35:04.450
But within the last 24 hours,
the sergeant has been pardoned

35:04.493 --> 35:06.147
for his actions in Afghanistan,

35:06.191 --> 35:08.323
so he no longer has
a Fifth Amendment right.

35:08.367 --> 35:09.387
- He must answer.
- Your Honor...

35:09.411 --> 35:10.543
The Supreme Court precedent

35:10.586 --> 35:12.545
is Burdick v. United States.

35:12.588 --> 35:15.069
The relevant passages are there.

35:16.723 --> 35:19.073
Recall Sergeant Meyer.

35:23.208 --> 35:25.166
Sergeant, isn't it true

35:25.210 --> 35:27.777
that Mr. Ahmad Mowad was shot

35:27.821 --> 35:30.128
in the afternoon
around 3:00 p.m.?

35:30.171 --> 35:31.955
Uh... 1500 hours?

35:31.999 --> 35:33.957
I plead the Fifth,
same as before.

35:34.001 --> 35:36.569
You must answer
the questions, Sergeant.

35:36.612 --> 35:38.179
You have
no Fifth Amendment right.

35:41.487 --> 35:45.099
So it's true you shot
Mr. Mowadat 1500 hours?

35:47.667 --> 35:49.712
- Affirmative.
- And Corporal Laney

35:49.756 --> 35:52.672
has admitted to taking
your gunaround dinnertime

35:52.715 --> 35:54.630
the evening before.
Can you confirm that he had

35:54.674 --> 35:55.954
access to your gun at that time?

35:55.979 --> 35:57.503
- Yes.
- And at no other time

35:57.546 --> 35:59.200
before Mr. Mowad was killed?

35:59.244 --> 36:01.550
- That's right.
- I have a document here

36:01.594 --> 36:03.465
stating that you practice

36:03.509 --> 36:05.641
- every morning with your gun.
- Objection.

36:05.685 --> 36:07.208
Trial counsel
has not been given a copy

36:07.252 --> 36:09.055
- of this mysterious document.
- This is a transcript

36:09.079 --> 36:11.125
of your opening statement,
Major.

36:11.169 --> 36:14.520
I'm assuming you told the truth.

36:14.563 --> 36:16.522
Overruled, Major.

36:16.565 --> 36:19.655
Actually, we did more
than assume; we checked.

36:19.699 --> 36:24.007
The AAMS keeps a log
of bullets used

36:24.051 --> 36:25.487
during target practice.

36:25.531 --> 36:29.012
Sergeant, isn't this your name
right here,

36:29.056 --> 36:31.232
practicing on the morning
that Mr. Mowad was killed?

36:31.276 --> 36:32.842
- Yes.
- So you knew

36:32.886 --> 36:35.715
that your gun was working fine
that morning,

36:35.758 --> 36:38.674
whatever Corporal Laney did
the night before?

36:38.718 --> 36:39.849
- No.
- Sergeant.

36:39.893 --> 36:41.677
Before you continue,

36:41.721 --> 36:44.550
uh, please understand
that you were only pardoned

36:44.593 --> 36:46.813
for your actions in Afghanistan.

36:46.856 --> 36:48.989
And if you lie
on the stand today,

36:49.032 --> 36:50.599
that's a new crime:

36:50.643 --> 36:52.079
perjury.

36:52.122 --> 36:54.212
And that's why
the prosecutor's here.

36:54.255 --> 36:56.910
So you knew
that your gun was working fine

36:56.953 --> 36:59.608
when you shot the translator?

37:00.653 --> 37:02.220
Sergeant?

37:04.874 --> 37:06.920
I may... I may have.

37:06.963 --> 37:08.922
Nothing further.

37:11.751 --> 37:14.710
Sergeant, the difference
betweena civilian and a combatant

37:14.754 --> 37:16.277
isn't quite as clear
in Afghanistan

37:16.321 --> 37:17.931
as we might imagine, is it?

37:17.974 --> 37:19.933
- No, it isn't.
- For example,

37:19.976 --> 37:21.935
don't terrorists send children
and the elderly

37:21.978 --> 37:24.024
to find American sniper nests,

37:24.067 --> 37:25.721
assuming we'll be
too squeamish to shoot,

37:25.765 --> 37:27.941
so they can use that
informationto set traps

37:27.984 --> 37:30.160
- for our soldiers?
- That is correct.

37:30.204 --> 37:33.120
In this tweet, President Trump
calls you a warrior...

37:33.163 --> 37:34.904
-Objection.-This is our commander in chief,

37:34.948 --> 37:37.864
Your Honor, speaking to an issue
pertinent to this court.

37:37.907 --> 37:39.953
Ask your question.

37:39.996 --> 37:42.129
President Trump calls you
a warrior, Sergeant,

37:42.172 --> 37:46.089
and says, "I see nothing wrongwith
how Sergeant Meyer behaved.

37:46.133 --> 37:48.831
"He was only doing his duty.

37:48.875 --> 37:52.095
We need our warriors
to be tough these days."

37:52.139 --> 37:53.575
Do you believe...

37:53.619 --> 37:55.751
Corporal Laney,
your subordinate,

37:55.795 --> 37:57.884
not only disobeyed orders

37:57.927 --> 38:01.017
but prevented you
from doing your duty?

38:01.061 --> 38:02.671
Yes.

38:02.715 --> 38:04.978
Nothing further.

38:05.979 --> 38:07.720
Well?

38:07.763 --> 38:09.287
I can't tell.

38:18.383 --> 38:19.775
There you go.

38:19.819 --> 38:21.951
- What's this?
- A file.

38:21.995 --> 38:23.823
- For what?
- Some case.

38:26.086 --> 38:27.870
Well...?

38:27.914 --> 38:29.089
Well, what?

38:29.132 --> 38:30.743
Tell me. What'd you do?

38:30.786 --> 38:33.006
I... helped her buy a resort.

38:33.049 --> 38:35.356
You're kidding.
Oh, my God.

38:35.400 --> 38:37.010
But I'm still
the better friend, right?

38:37.053 --> 38:38.968
Always.
So, I have a question for you.

38:39.012 --> 38:40.622
Hit me.

38:41.710 --> 38:43.364
I won some money playing poker,

38:43.408 --> 38:45.801
- and she lent me my stake.
- How much?

38:45.845 --> 38:48.804
- How much did she lend?
- No, how much did you win?

38:50.371 --> 38:52.330
Fifteen hundred.

38:52.373 --> 38:54.636
Oh. Well,
that was anticlimactic.

38:54.680 --> 38:57.639
But she lent me the money
to bet, so...

38:57.683 --> 38:59.902
shouldn't I give her
all the winnings?

38:59.946 --> 39:02.165
No. She doesn't need $1,500.

39:02.209 --> 39:04.167
- Keep it.
- What if it's a lot more?

39:04.211 --> 39:05.821
Don't ask me how much.

39:05.865 --> 39:07.127
- Okay?
- Okay.

39:07.170 --> 39:09.347
- How much?
- No matter how much money,

39:09.390 --> 39:11.653
- I should give it all
to her, right?
- No.

39:11.697 --> 39:13.176
If you feel guilty,
get her a gift.

39:13.220 --> 39:14.874
Something a rich person needs.

39:14.917 --> 39:16.658
What does a rich person need?

39:16.702 --> 39:17.877
Love.

39:23.186 --> 39:25.711
Have you, um... started?

39:28.061 --> 39:29.671
- Mm.
- All rise.

39:29.715 --> 39:31.847
- You look calmer.
- Well...

39:31.891 --> 39:33.675
what have we got?

39:33.719 --> 39:35.416
Lonergan vs. Syncrest, Inc.

39:35.460 --> 39:36.896
Eminent domain.

39:36.939 --> 39:38.898
Ah. Counselors,

39:38.941 --> 39:40.682
welcome back.

39:40.726 --> 39:42.162
Is everybody ready to get going?

39:42.205 --> 39:44.251
- Yes, Your Honor.
- Actually, Your Honor,

39:44.294 --> 39:46.340
my client is unable
to be here today.

39:46.384 --> 39:48.081
- Aw. Why is that?
- He's in New York

39:48.124 --> 39:50.213
ringing the opening bell
at the stock exchange.

39:50.257 --> 39:52.781
- Oh. Impressive.
- Your Honor,

39:52.825 --> 39:55.741
the defendant is still harming
my client's business.

39:55.784 --> 39:57.806
You're suggesting, Counselor,
that any further delays

39:57.830 --> 39:59.745
- might be prejudicial?
- Yes,

39:59.788 --> 40:01.790
- and if I may explain...
- No need.

40:01.834 --> 40:04.097
I agree.
Injunction granted.

40:04.140 --> 40:06.447
- Your Honor, if I...
- No. You had 24 hours

40:06.491 --> 40:08.449
to present your client...
You failed.

40:08.493 --> 40:10.756
Judgment for the plaintiff.

40:12.758 --> 40:14.281
Congratulations.

40:17.327 --> 40:18.764
Well, thank you, Diane.

40:18.807 --> 40:20.766
I think he saw you over here.

40:21.810 --> 40:23.986
No, I don't think that was it.

40:28.121 --> 40:29.514
Enter.

40:31.298 --> 40:33.256
Diane. What's up?

40:33.300 --> 40:35.389
I think you and I
should have lunch.

40:35.433 --> 40:37.913
- Why?
- To trade information

40:37.957 --> 40:39.959
about Memo 618.

40:47.096 --> 40:49.098
So, what do you think?

40:49.142 --> 40:51.318
I can never tell.

40:52.493 --> 40:55.540
Have you reached a verdict?

41:07.813 --> 41:09.815
Corporal Laney, please stand.

41:11.164 --> 41:13.296
On the charge
of negligent homicide,

41:13.340 --> 41:16.299
the panel finds the defendant,
Army Corporal Demarcus Laney,

41:16.343 --> 41:17.518
not guilty.

41:17.562 --> 41:19.781
On the charge
of insubordination,

41:19.825 --> 41:21.217
not guilty.
And on the charge

41:21.261 --> 41:24.133
of damage to military property, guilty.

41:24.177 --> 41:27.876
The panel imposes a sentence
of time served.

41:27.920 --> 41:29.399
Corporal Laney, you may go.

41:29.443 --> 41:33.099
- Court adjourned.
- Attention!

41:37.190 --> 41:40.236
- Nice work.
- You, too.

41:40.280 --> 41:42.500
- Feels good to win for a change.-

41:45.328 --> 41:47.505
You have to get home to Malcolm?

41:47.548 --> 41:49.507
Oh, uh...

41:49.550 --> 41:52.161
no, Malcolm is, uh,
with his father tonight.

41:52.205 --> 41:54.294
Want to grab dinner?

41:55.338 --> 41:57.210
♪

42:09.396 --> 42:10.919
What are we doing?

42:10.963 --> 42:12.486
We're experimenting.

42:12.530 --> 42:13.835
Yeah.

42:13.879 --> 42:15.881
♪

42:20.450 --> 42:22.409
How much?

42:22.452 --> 42:24.150
Without the frills.

42:24.193 --> 42:26.544
Someone left a gift for you.

42:26.587 --> 42:28.546
♪

42:30.243 --> 42:32.027
No. Come to me in good faith,

42:32.071 --> 42:33.855
and I might change my mind.

42:33.899 --> 42:36.031
I'll call you back.

